ing 210,803\ngalaxies in just 32 days of GZ2 project time with 93.1% accuracy. As the Random\nForest algorithm requires a minimal amount of computation cost, this result has\nimportant implications for galaxy morphology identification tasks in the era of\nEuclid and other large scale surveys.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Feb 2018 19:43:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-21"}
